Ethereum ADL Model

Download Proper Dependencies

library(‘strucchange’) library(‘dynlm’) library(‘xts’) library(‘zoo’) library(‘AER’) library(‘Rcpp’) library(‘lmtest’) library(‘plm’) library(‘data.table’) library(‘sandwich’) library(‘glue’) library(‘car’) library(tidyverse) library(stargazer); require(broom)
library(magrittr)

Clean Data

df = read.csv('eth_for_reg.csv')
df <- xts(df[,colnames(df)!="Week"], order.by=as.Date(df$Week,"%Y-%m-%d"))
df$AvgFeeUsd_growth <- diff(log(df$AvgFeeUsd))
df$AvgTxCnt_growth <- diff(log(df$AvgTxCnt))
df$AvgPriceUSD_growth <- diff(log(df$AvgPriceUSD))
df$Interest_growth <- diff(log(df$Interest))

Plot Data to 2X Check it is Staionary

plot(as.zoo(df$AvgFeeUsd_growth),
  col = "steelblue",
  lwd = 2,
  ylab = "AvgFeeUsd_growth",
  xlab = "Date",

Run AR Models to find proper lag length

## t test of coefficients:
##

Given the chosen model, look for a structural break using QLR

Note that the break is too close to the end so we will not run our final ADL model with only data following this break

df$AvgFeeUsd_growth_l1<- stats::lag(df$AvgFeeUsd_growth,k=1,na.pad=T)

F_values <- Fstats(AvgFeeUsd_growth ~ AvgFeeUsd_growth_l1 + Interest_growth + AvgPriceUSD_growth, data = as.data.frame(df), from = 0.15, to = 0.85, vcov = function(x, ...) vcovHC(x, type = "HC", ...))
F_values$breakpoint

plot(F_values$Fstats)
lines(breakpoints(F_values))

Settle on on a model

forecast_model <- dynlm(AvgFeeUsd_growth ~ L(AvgFeeUsd_growth) + L(AvgPriceUSD_growth) + L(Interest_growth),data=ts(df))
coeftest(forecast_model, vcov = vcovHC(forecast_model,type="HC1"))
## 
## t test of coefficients:
##

linearHypothesis(forecast_model,c("L(AvgFeeUsd_growth)=0","L(Interest_growth)=0"),white.adjust="hc1")
